// Audit Task 142 (Tier 2): Hill Mari — sister of Meadow Mari (mhr).
LANG_DATA['mrj'].meta = { family:'Uralic (Mari)', speakers:'~30K', countries:'Russia (Mari El)', official:'Republic of Mari El (co-official)', script:'Cyrillic (with ӓ ӧ ӱ ҥ ӹ)', description:{en:'Hill Mari (Western Mari) is the smaller of the two Mari literary standards, spoken on the western (right) bank of the Volga around Kozmodemyansk. Hill and Meadow Mari are partly mutually intelligible but standardised separately; both are co-official in the Republic of Mari El.',ja:'山地マリ語（西マリ語）はマリ語の2つの文章語標準のうちの小さい方で、ヴォルガ川西岸（右岸）のコズモデミヤンスク周辺で話される。山地マリ語と草原マリ語は部分的に相互理解可能だが標準化は別々であり、両者ともマリ・エル共和国の共和国共通語となっている。',ko:'산악 마리어(서부 마리어)는 마리어의 두 문어 표준 중 작은 쪽으로, 볼가강 서안(우안) 코즈모데미얀스크 일대에서 사용된다. 산악 마리어와 초원 마리어는 부분적으로 상호 이해 가능하나 표준화는 별개로 이루어졌으며, 양자 모두 마리 엘 공화국의 공용어이다.',zh:'山地马里语（西马里语）是马里语两种文学标准中较小的一种，使用于伏尔加河西岸（右岸）科兹莫杰米扬斯克周边。山地马里语与草原马里语部分可互通但分别被标准化，两者皆为马里埃尔共和国的共和国官方语言。'}, sources:[{type:'reference', title:'Glottolog: Hill Mari', url:'https://glottolog.org/resource/languoid/id/hill1247'}, {type:'reference', title:'Ethnologue: mrj', url:'https://www.ethnologue.com/language/mrj/'}] };
LANG_DATA['myv'].meta = { family:'Uralic (Mordvinic)', speakers:'~120K', countries:'Russia (Mordovia)', official:'Republic of Mordovia (co-official)', script:'Cyrillic', description:{en:'Erzya is one of two Mordvinic languages (with Moksha), historically spoken by the Erzya people of the middle Volga. The two Mordvinic languages are not mutually intelligible despite both being state languages of Mordovia.'} };
